Well, today I flew.
First criticism: We need prettier logbooks. Black is boring, pink is not really pink but more salmon-colored.
I wanted to fly since I was little.
And today it finally happened... I flew an airplane today. I haven't quite processed that yet.
Data from FlightAware.
I am trying to fly again next Saturday. The weather does not look good right now, but it is only Monday.
It is already becoming clear where the problems lie. It will likely be extremely difficult to get medical clearance, due to the FAA's opinion on certain medications.
It is not impossible, but it will take VERY long and mean a LOT of extra work.
This is somewhat discouraging, but still just another problem that needs to be solved. So far, it seems solvable. It just takes a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what lies ahead for me.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. They definitely will not give you medical clearance if you take medication for it.
